Introduction to HTML

HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language used to create and design web pages. It provides the structure of a webpage by using tags and elements to define headings, paragraphs, links, images, tables, forms, and other content.

HyperText: Refers to the way web pages are linked together using hyperlinks.

Markup Language: Uses tags to "mark up" text so that browsers can display it properly.

Key Features of HTML:

Structure Content: Organizes content into headings, paragraphs, lists, tables, etc.

Hyperlinking: Allows linking to other pages or websites.

Embedding Media: Supports images, audio, video, and other multimedia elements.

Forms & Input: Enables user interaction through forms.

Cross-platform: HTML files can be viewed on any device with a web browser.
